The documentation in this tree is in plain text fields and can be viewed using
your favorite text file viewer.

It uses ReST (reStructuredText) [1] and the Sphinx documentation system [2].

To create an HTML version of these docs:

* Install Sphinx (which can be done using python by running ``pip install Sphinx``)

* In docs/, run ``make html`` (or ``make.bat html`` on Windows) at a shell prompt

The documentation can be viewed using a web browser by opening _build/html/index.html

